data04_2 <- read.csv("./causality-main/data04.csv")
attach(data04_2)
y0obs <- na.omit(y0)  # 
y1obs <- na.omit(y1)  # 
n0 <- length(y0obs)   # 
n1 <- length(y1obs)   # 
s0 <- sd(y0obs)       # 
s1 <- sd(y1obs)       # 
num <- (s1^2/n1 + s0^2/n0)^2                         # 4.16(numerator)
denom <- ((s1^2/n1)^2)/(n1-1) + ((s0^2/n0)^2)/(n0-1) # 4.16(denominator)
df1 <- num/denom      # 
xbar <- mean(y1obs) - mean(y0obs)       # y1obsy0obs
se1 <- sqrt((s1^2/n1) + (s0^2/n0))      # 
talph <- qt(0.025, df1, lower.tail = F) # 95%
xbar + talph * se1    # 95%
    ## [1] 18.46937
    xbar - talph * se1# 95%
    ## [1] 3.447297
    t.test(y1obs, y0obs, var.equal=FALSE)

##  Welch Two Sample t-test
